BINARY HACK THING- converts a given number (20) to binary!
1st part- conversion function- a number to binary
2nd part- the binary number (array storing thing)
3rd part- the counter for the array
4th part- storing the stuff
5th part- printing stuff
6th part- definition to use in variables throughout code

def decToBinary(n):

    binaryNum = [0] * n;


    i = 0;
    while (n > 0):


        binaryNum[i] = n % 2;
        n = int(n / 2);
        i += 1;


    for j in range(i - 1, -1, -1):
        print(binaryNum[j], end = "");


n = 20;
decToBinary(n);

